NameFlagsCard.TypeDescription & Constraints
UnEMREncounterModel 0..*UnEMR Encounter Logical Model
encounterId 1..1idIdentifier for this encounter
typeOfEncounter 0..1CodeableConceptType of consultation
purposeOfEncounter 0..1CodeableConceptPurpose of consulration
dateOfEncounter 1..1dateTimeDate of the consultation
patient 1..1Reference()Reference to the patient
provider 1..1Reference()Reference to the provider
age 0..1integerAge of the patient on consultation
complaints 0..*CodeableConceptIssues identified by the patient
reviewOfSystems 0..1BackboneElementReview of systems
neurologic 0..1stringReview of the neurologic system
pulmonary 0..1stringReview of the pulmonary system
cardiovascular 0..1stringReview of the cardiovascular system
skinAndGlands 0..1stringReview of the skin and glands
gastrointestinal 0..1stringReview of the gastrointestinal system
muscoloskeletal 0..1stringReview of the muscoloskeletal system
psychiatric 0..1stringPsychiatric review
gcs 0..1BackboneElementGlascow coma scale scoring
eyeResponse 0..1stringEye response GCS scoring
verbalResponse 0..1stringVerbal response GCS scoring
motorResponse 0..1stringMotor response GCS scoring
vitals 0..1BackboneElementPatient vital signs
temperature 0..1stringPatient temperature during consultation
bloodPressure 0..1stringPatient blood pressure during consultation
pulseRate 0..1stringPatient pulse rate during consultation
oxygenation 0..1stringPatient blood oxygenation levels during consultation
respirationRate 0..1stringPatient respiration rate during consultation
height 0..1stringPatient height during consultation
weight 0..1stringPatient weight during consultation
bmi 0..1integerPatient body mass index
physicalExam 0..1BackboneElementPatient physical examination results
heent 0..1stringHEENT physical examination results
cardiovascular 0..1stringPatient cardiovascular system
pulmonary 0..1stringPatient pulmonary system
gastrointestinal 0..1stringPatient gastrointestinal system
reproductive 0..1stringPatient reproductive system
extremities 0..1stringPatient extremities
skin 0..1stringPatient skin
genitourinary 0..1stringPatient genitourinary system
nervous 0..1stringPatient nervous system
mse 0..1BackboneElementPatient mental state examination
motor 0..1stringPatient mental motor state results
speech 0..1stringPatient speech
affect 0..1stringPatient mental affect
thoughtContent 0..1stringPatient thought content
thoughtProcess 0..1stringPatient thought process
perception 0..1stringPatient perception
intellect 0..1stringPatient intellectual
insight 0..1stringPatient insight
confidentialNotes 0..1stringAdditional confidential or phychiatric-medicolegal notes
procedures 0..*CodeableConceptPatient treatment plan and procedures
prescriptions 0..*CodeableConceptMedication prescribed by the provider to the patient
outcomeOfTreatment 0..1CodeableConceptDescribes whether the treatment was successful or not
auditLog 1..1BackboneElementRecord audit log
createdBy 1..1Reference()Person who created the record
dateCreated 1..1dateTimeDate when the encounter record was created
lastUpdatedBy 1..1Reference()Person who recently updated the record
dateLastUpdated 1..1dateTimeDate when the encounter record last updated

Documentation for this format

name: UnEMREncounterModel
title: UnEMR Encounter Logical Model
publisher: University of San Agustin - Center for Informatics
description: Encounter data model implemented in UnEMR

element.definition: Encounter data model implemented in UnEMR
Type of medical consultation (e.g. outpatient, inpatient, emergency)
Purpose of the consultation (e.g. check-up, follow-up, new health issue)
Provider who is involved with this patient consultation

element.short: Age of the patient on consultation
element.definition: Age of the patient during the consultation
Issues identified by the patient. Values are selected from SNOMED-CT or ICD-10

element.short: Review of the skin and glands
element.definition: Review of the skin and glands

element.short: Patient blood oxygenation levels during consultation
element.definition: Patient blood oxygenation levels during consultation
Physical examination results on the patient's cardiovascular system
Physical examination results on the patient's pulmonary system
Physical examination results on the patient's gastrointestinal system
Physical examination results on the patient's reproductive system
Physical examination results on the patient's extremities
Physical examination results on the patient's skin
Physical examination results on the patient's genitourinary system
Physical examination results on the patient's nervous system
Patient treatment plan and procedures. Values may be selected from SNOMED-CT

element.short: Medication prescribed by the provider to the patient
element.definition: Medication prescribed by the provider to the patient. Values may be selected from SNOMED-CT

element.short: Describes whether the treatment was successful or not
element.definition: Describes whether the treatment was successful or not. Options are either positive, negative, or no change
Person who created the encounter record

element.short: Date when the encounter record was created
element.definition: Date when the encounter record was created

element.short: Person who recently updated the record
element.definition: Person who recently updated the record

element.short: Date when the encounter record last updated
element.definition: Date when the encounter record last updated
